<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="192" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                        <head>No. 188.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L.
                                    West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-06-02"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 2, 1886</date>.
                                [Received June 3.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your notes of the 20th and 29th of May on the subject of the
                            seizure of American fishing vessels in Canadian waters.</p>
                        <p>I have, &amp;c.</p>
                        <closer><signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>